                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/584: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Geissler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-19T18:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1928—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Referring to the Department’s telegram of March 17, 7 p.m.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d517fn2">See footnote 1, <ref target="#pg_722">p. 722</ref>.</note>
                    The President is out of town but is expected to return tonight.</p>
                <p>The Acting Minister for Foreign Affairs says that Carlos Salazar, delegate to the
                    recent Pan American Conference,<note n="3" xml:id="d517fn3">See <ref
                            target="#pg_527">pp. 527</ref> ff.</note> and two engineers will be
                    appointed Commissioners but that no decision has been reached as to when and
                    where it is desirable for the Commission to meet. I shall talk with the
                    President tomorrow.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tegucigalpa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geissler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
